      "amount": "1/2 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "Dum Dum Dum Mix",
      "amount": "3 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "Lemon Juice",
      "amount": "1 tablespoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "Salt to taste"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat coconut oil or avocado oil in a pan over medium heat.",
    "Add minced garlic and cook until fragrant, about 2 minutes.",
    "Stir in tomato paste and cook for another minute.",
    "Add baby plum tomatoes, red pepper flakes (if using), and salt. Stir well to combine.",
    "Pour in the dum dum dum mix and add lemon juice. Mix everything together thoroughly.",
    "Reduce heat to low and let simmer for 5-7 minutes until the sauce has thickened slightly.",
    "Serve hot as a side dish or over rice."
